commit.message:
Increase upper bound on interfaces to 128 (#24)

We hit the limit of 64 interfaces when running a large number of
`docker` containers, each of which created a bridge interface.  This
doubles the limit as a temporary work-around, although a real fix
would be to change the code to handle an arbitrarily large number of
interfaces as memory permits.

commit.message:
Fix segmentation fault for more than 64 interfaces (#23)

`getifaddrs` can return a linked list of more than `max_ns`
interfaces, and when that happens `add_interface` will begin to
return `NULL` when the `ns` array is full.

This fixes that by breaking from the loop when `add_interface` fails,
truncating the results to `max_ns` entries.

commit.message:
Depending in PF potentially breaks FreeBSD build.

Not all FreeBSD systems do have PF as a packet filter installed. Depending on `net/pf/pfvar.h` breaks the build
on these systems.

commit.message:
Support cross-compiling

Use the workaround mentioned on the GHC Trac [1] for the lack let
directives when cross-compiling.

1. https://ghc.haskell.org/trac/ghc/ticket/10272

Add DragonflyBSD support.

I just copied this out of the dragonfly hs-network-info package,
which credits "haskell@freebsd.org".

Fix build on Hurd

Build broken by 7faccfa. At the moment SIOCGARP is not defined on Hurd.
Removed -Werror due to clang reporting hard to fix warnings #7
Don't ARP for MAC on loopback
